<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - REASSEMBLE - REMOTE CONTROL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOTE CONTROL</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13016_10.xml" xrefid="f1301603">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new key into the rod and bracket assembly. Install the assembly into the remote
                housing, sliding the shift finger (inner shaft) on the end of the rod.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Line up the setscrew hole and install the setscrew. Tighten it to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68
                N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the U-joint shift rod through cross holes and outer finger, making sure the finger
                is inserted into the bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the setscrew holes and install the setscrew. Tighten it to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68
                N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the end cover and gasket. Secure it with four bolts and lockwashers. Tighten to 34
                to 41 ft-lbs. (46 to 56 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two new oil seals in the U-joint shift rod bores.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the U-joint assembly. Secure it with a setscrew.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
